  |     Summary                                                             |
  |   -------------------------------------------------------------------   |
  |                                                                         |
  |   True Fear: Forsaken Souls combines the best of the psychological      |
  |   thriller with intuitive gameplay mechanics for a mind-bending         |
  |   mystery escape game.                                                  |
  |                                                                         |
  |   If you're looking for a horror game that doesn’t sacrifice the        |
  |   story, this is the game for you!                                      |
  |                                                                         |
  |   Skeptical that a point and click adventure can be compelling or       |
  |   scary?s                                                               |
  |                                                                         |
  |   Features:                                                             |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * An intense adventure brimming with psychological suspense in a      |
  |     plot filled with twists and turns.                                  |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Choose your adventure! Play with or without the hidden object       |
  |     scenes.                                                             |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Play using Joy-Cons, Pro Controller or touch screen.                |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Unlock 40 achievements, find 15 collectibles.                       |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Includes the bonuses from the Collector's version of True Fear:     |
  |     Forsaken Soul: an additional level, wallpapers, making of and       |
  |     deleted content.                                                    |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * True Fear: Forsaken Souls Part I is the first game of the           |
  |     trilogy.                                                            |
